''See also [[submergé]]''
==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[submergere]]'', from ''[[sub-#Latin|sub-]]'' ("under") + ''[[mergere]]'' ("to plunge").

===Verb===
{{en-verb|submerge|submerges|submerged|submerging}}

#''(intransitive)'' To [[sink]] out of [[sight]].
#:''The submarine submerged in the water.''
#''(transitive)'' To [[put]] into a [[liquid]]; to [[immerse]]; to [[plunge]] into and keep in.
#:''In films many people are murdered by being submerged in a swimming pool.''

====Synonyms====
*[[immerse]] (2)

====Translations====
*German: [[abtauchen]] (1), [[untertauchen]] (2)
*Japanese: [[沈む]] ([[しずむ]], shizumú) (1), [[沈める]] ([[しずめる]], shizumerú) (2)
*Turkish: [[batmak]] (1), [[batırmak]] (2)

====Derived terms====
*[[submergence]]
*[[submersion]]

